    <abstract id="aspace_f84ec76acd5214a157e5fa08a8647992">Brent Kramer was an employee of the New York Telephone Company and member of the Communications Workers of America (CWA), Local 1101. This collection contains records of Brent Kramer and several of his colleagues' rank-and-file activities in Communications Workers of America Local 1101 from 1970 to the 1990s. CWA Local 1101 represented Bell System (and later Verizon) technical workers in Manhattan and the Bronx. The materials cover the strikes of 1971 and 1989, the <emph render="italic"> Newman v. Local 1101, Communications Workers of America</emph> lawsuit, and Local 1101 elections.</abstract>
    <physloc id="aspace_17b6c3b4dd131de5399916c6fe1b9607">Materials are stored offsite and advance notice is required for use. Please request materials at least two business days prior to your research visit to coordinate access.</physloc>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_6d7dd983e0afb846c9b320ed37de3f60">Materials are in English.</langmaterial>
  </did>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_e2780ef7ba721054f22319848dc8a4a7">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>This collection contains records of Brent Kramer and several of his colleagues' rank-and-file activities in Communications Workers of America (CWA), Local 1101 from 1970 to the 1990s. CWA Local 1101 represented Bell System (and later Verizon) technical workers in Manhattan and the Bronx.</p><p>Materials include various union publications such as newspapers, newsletters, flyers, leaflets, pamphlets, and circulars. Some publications include <emph render="italic">Ring Down</emph>, <emph render="italic">New York Generator</emph>, <emph render="italic">Final Warning</emph>, <emph render="italic">Against the Grain</emph>, <emph render="italic">The Bell Wringer</emph>, and <emph render="italic">Labor Notes</emph>. Also included are correspondence, notes, article drafts, layouts, sample ballots, legal files related to <emph render="italic">Newman v. Local 1101, Communications Workers of America</emph> (a case in which he was also a plaintiff), mailers, a Teamsters for a Democratic Union (TDU) conference program, newspaper clippings, nomination petitions, and a sign from the 1989 NYNEX strike. </p>  </scopecontent>
  <arrangement id="aspace_84034ef0b2ffd98de363ec6ab9563d7a">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>This collection has not been arranged by an archivist. The materials are arranged in the order in which they were received from the donor.</p>  </arrangement>
